Simple "Ask Beast" Siri Shortcut (Best Current Method)

This creates:

"Hey Siri, Ask Beast"

which:

* opens ChatGPT
* sends your spoken question
* uses your actual ChatGPT account + Beast2 context/memory

No coding required.

⸻

Step 1 -- Open Shortcuts

Open the Shortcuts app.

Tap:

* + (top right)
* "Add Action"

⸻

Step 2 -- Add "Ask for Input"

Search:

* Ask for Input

Add it.

Configure:

* Input Type: Text
* Prompt:
    Ask Beast

This makes Siri listen for your spoken question.

⸻

Step 3 -- Add "Ask ChatGPT"

Tap:

* "Search Actions"

Search:

* Ask ChatGPT

Add it.

Set:

* Message = Provided Input

Important:

* Do NOT type fixed text
* It must use the variable from Step 2

It should visually show:

Ask ChatGPT with [Provided Input]

⸻

Step 4 -- Enable Voice Phrase

Tap:

* dropdown arrow near shortcut name
    OR
* the shortcut title at top

Rename shortcut:

Ask Beast

Now Siri trigger becomes:

"Hey Siri, Ask Beast"

⸻

Step 5 -- Optional Better Version (Recommended)

Instead of only:

"Define Beast2"

you can prepend context automatically.

In the "Ask ChatGPT" field, use:

You are Beast, assistant for the Beast2 and Beast3 projects.

User request:
[Provided Input]

This improves reliability because ChatGPT receives a stronger framing every time.

⸻

Step 6 -- Test

Say:

"Hey Siri, Ask Beast"

Then after Siri pauses:

"Define Beast2"

